{
  "monologue": "Your profile shows high sensitivity to evening cues and a strong need for structure. A single, reliably executed micro-action after a brief craving pause helps anchor the response without overwhelming you. By tying this to immediate logging, you convert craving energy into a small, repeatable win, which steadily nudges you toward the target behavior through consistent, manageable steps.",
  "utterance": "Tonight, after your 60-second craving pause, pick one micro-action you can finish in under 2 minutes and log it right away. Try one of these fresh options: a 30-second body scan with a 1-minute slow-breath cycle, a quick 1-minute upper-body stretch, or a 90-second in-place walk. Keep a simple plan handy (phone reminder or sticky note) so you can act immediately when cravings hit. If the craving remains strong, repeat the micro-action once or extend to 2 minutes, then log again. Remember: small, consistent steps beat big leaps.",
  "endkey": false
}
